
1) What is the difference between the Thread and Runnable?
Thread is a class and runnable is an interface

2) How do you start a thread using Runnable?
you define a method called run() in the implementing class and after making a new thread you call start()
3) How do you start a thread using Thread?
make a class that extends thread. In it override the run method and call start in the constructor

4) How do you get a thread's name?
give the class an instance variable for name and access that variable

5) What does the synchronize do?
it makes it so a shared resource can only be accessed by one thread at a time so another thread trying to access the resource will
be in a suspended state until the prior thread is done


6) What doe the "join()" method do?
The calling thread will wait for the specified thread to finish before continuing


7) What does the "sleep()" method do?
it suspends the the calling thread for the specified amount of milliseconds

8) What is the one method you must write if you're implementing the Runnable class?
run()


9) Should you create that same method if you're extending Thread?
you can but are not required to


10) Why is multi-threading so cool?
Allows your programs to multi task an ddo other tasks in the background that are not dependent on another thread. Can be faster.

